    "reasoning": "To implement the required finite state machine (FSM) for HDLC framing, we need to recognize specific bit patterns: 0111110 (disc), 01111110 (flag), and 01111111... (err). The FSM should have states to track consecutive 1s and detect these patterns. We'll use a Moore-type FSM where outputs depend only on the current state. States will be designed such that they correctly identify the required patterns. The initial state after reset will treat the previous input as 0, so we initialize appropriately. A state diagram approach is used to transition between states based on input bits. We'll need to track the last few bits to detect 5 consecutive 1s, 6 consecutive 1s, and 7 or more 1s. For this, we use shift registers to store history of input bits. The output signals (disc, flag, err) will be set according to the detected patterns. The FSM will be implemented using always blocks for sequential and combinational logic.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input reset,\n    input in,\n    output reg disc,\n    output reg flag,\n    output reg err\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam S_RESET = 3'b000;\n    localparam S_IDLE = 3'b001;\n    localparam S_ONE = 3'b010;\n    localparam S_TWO = 3'b011;\n    localparam S_THREE = 3'b100;\n    localparam S_FOUR = 3'b101;\n    localparam S_FIVE = 3'b110;\n    localparam S_SIX = 3'b111;\n\n    // Current and next state\n    logic [2:0] current_state, next_state;\n\n    // Shift register for tracking previous 6 bits\n    logic [5:0] shift_reg;\n\n    // Initialize state to S_RESET\n    initial begin\n        current_state = S_RESET;\n    end\n\n    // Sequential logic for state and shift register\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset) begin\n            current_state <= S_RESET;\n            shift_reg <= 6'b000000;\n        end else begin\n            current_state <= next_state;\n            shift_reg <= {shift_reg[4:0], in};\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state and outputs\n    always @(*) begin\n        // Default assignments\n        next_state = current_state;\n        disc = 1'b0;\n        flag = 1'b0;\n        err = 1'b0;\n\n        case (current_state)\n            S_RESET: begin\n                next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_IDLE: begin\n                if (in)\n                    next_state = S_ONE;\n                else\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_ONE: begin\n                if (in)\n                    next_state = S_TWO;\n                else\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_TWO: begin\n                if (in)\n                    next_state = S_THREE;\n                else\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_THREE: begin\n                if (in)\n                    next_state = S_FOUR;\n                else\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_FOUR: begin\n                if (in)\n                    next_state = S_FIVE;\n                else\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_FIVE: begin\n                if (in)\n                    next_state = S_SIX;\n                else\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n            end\n            \n            S_SIX: begin\n                if (in) begin\n                    // 7 or more 1s\n                    next_state = S_SIX;\n                    err = 1'b1;\n                end else begin\n                    // Exactly 6 ones, 0111110 - flag is not triggered yet, but 0111110 indicates we're in a valid state\n                    // This is a special case, we consider it as a discard\n                    next_state = S_IDLE;\n                    disc = 1'b1;\n                end\n            end\n        endcase\n\n        // Special check for 01111110 pattern\n        if (shift_reg == 6'b011111) begin\n            flag = 1'b1;\n        end\n        \n        // Check for 0111110 pattern\n        if (shift_reg == 6'b011110) begin\n            disc = 1'b1;\n        end\n        \n        // Check for 7 or more 1s\n        if (shift_reg == 6'b111111) begin\n            err = 1'b1;\n        end\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
